 case against the Daily Mail publisher. They had accused the company of unlawful information-gathering methods over many years. The judge dismissed all claims, stating insufficient proof of wrongdoing was presented. The claimants now face a substantial legal bill of around fifty million pounds. Associated Newspapers Ltd welcomed the ruling, calling the claims preposterous and misguided.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/prince-harry-lost-his-daily-mail-case-now-a-50-million-legal-bill-may-be-the-bigger-story/articleshow/132260607.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/prince-harry-lost-his-daily-mail-case-now-a-50-million-legal-bill-may-be-the-bigger-story/articleshow/132260607.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-08T15:59:59+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132260665,imgsize-86396.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Is Connor Murphy dead or alive? What we know about the viral rumor surrounding the YouTube bodybuilder]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132250995.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Connor Murphy’s reported death remains an unconfirmed rumor as of July 2026. Claims circulating online largely stem from social media posts and statements that have not been independently verified. No family member, representative, or authority has confirmed his death. Murphy rose to fame through fitness and bodybuilding content, and questions about his current status remain unanswered pending official information.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us-streamers/is-connor-murphy-dead-or-alive-what-we-know-about-the-viral-rumor-surrounding-the-youtube-bodybuilder/articleshow/132250995.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.in